<section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="wrap">
        <header class="section-head">
            <p class="eyebrow">What I check</p>
            <h2>Areas I inspect for a complete evaluation</h2>
        </header>

        <div class="areas">
            <div class="area">
                <h3>Structural Integrity</h3>
                <p>The bones of the home — what holds everything up.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Foundation stability and signs of settlement</li>
                    <li>Walls, ceilings, and floors for cracks or damage</li>
                    <li>Basement, crawlspace, and beams for water intrusion or rot</li>
                    <li>Roof structure, trusses, and attic framing</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="area">
                <h3>Exterior Systems</h3>
                <p>The property's exterior is inspected for wear, damage, and potential issues.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Roofing materials, flashing, and gutters for leaks or damage</li>
                    <li>Siding, brickwork, and exterior finishes</li>
                    <li>Doors, windows, and seals for drafts and functionality</li>
                    <li>Drainage, grading, and walkways to prevent water intrusion</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="area">
                <h3>Interior Systems</h3>
                <p>Inside your property, I examine all major systems and living spaces for functionality and safety.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Walls, ceilings, and floors for damage or moisture signs</li>
                    <li>Windows and doors for alignment and seals</li>
                    <li>Staircases and railings for safety compliance</li>
                    <li>Kitchen appliances, cabinets, and fixtures</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="area">
                <h3>Mechanical &amp; Safety Systems</h3>
                <p>I evaluate the key systems that keep your property running smoothly.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>HVAC:</strong> heating, cooling, and ventilation systems for efficiency</li>
                    <li><strong>Electrical:</strong> outlets, wiring, breaker panels, and grounding</li>
                    <li><strong>Plumbing:</strong> pipes, fixtures, water heaters, and drainage</li>
                    <li><strong>Safety:</strong> fireplaces, smoke detectors, carbon monoxide alarms</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="area">
                <h3>Specialized Areas</h3>
                <p>Certain aspects require extra attention to protect your investment.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Attic insulation and ventilation for energy efficiency</li>
                    <li>Garage and outbuildings for structural soundness</li>
                    <li>Decks, balconies, and porches for stability and safety</li>
                    <li>Visible pest damage or signs of wood-destroying organisms</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="area">
                <h3>Detailed Reporting</h3>
                <p>Every inspection ends with a clear, photo-backed report.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Easy-to-read summary of findings, delivered within 24 hours</li>
